    "en": {
      "title": "Principals allowed to download A/L results",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "COLOMBO (News 1st); The Department of Education says school principals can download 2021 G.C.E Advanced Level results from Monday (29).",
        "Commissioner-General of Examinations L.M.D. Dharmasena said that applicants who wish to retake the A/L exam can submit applications online until the 8th of September.",
        "The GCE Advanced Level Examination 2021 results were released on Sunday (28).",
        "According to the Examinations Department, a total of 272,682 candidates sat for the A/L exam, out of which 171,497 candidates have qualified for university entrance.",
        "The results of 49 candidates were suspended, noted the Department of Examination."
      ],
